condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.G | Description :Under Part B.2 of the Project, the Recipient shall, no later than nine(9) months after the Effective Date, engage in accordance with the provisions of Section III of this Schedule 2 and thereaftermaintain, an EEA whose terms of reference, qualifications and experience shall be satisfactory to the Association, to monitor,evaluate and report on Part A(1) of the Project, and to conduct independent | Due Date :24-Jun-2016

Finance Agreement :Section 4.01 of the FA and GA | Description :Concomitant effectiveness of the FA and the GA once evidence ofvalidity and binding effect of both agreements have been received by the Bank | Due Date :28-Oct-2012

Finance Agreement :Section I.B.2(a) of Schedule 2 to the FA and GA | Description :The Recipient shall cause each PPA to finalize,in accordance with terms of reference acceptable to the Association and furnish to the Association for its approval, its PBF AgencyAgreement, the proposed PBF Manual included in the PPA's technical bid for services. | Due Date :30-Sep-2016

Finance Agreement :Section I.E.1 of Schedule 2 to FA and GA | Description :The Recipient shall furnish a program of activities forthe first year of Project implementation to the Association, for its reviewand approval by the Association | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section I.G of Schedule 2 to FA and GA | Description :The Recipient shall, engage and thereafter maintain, oneor more evaluation agencies (“External Evaluation Agency” or “EEA”) to monitor, evaluate and report on Part A (1) of the Project,and to conduct independent verifications of the delivery of Technical Support Packages and MCH Packages. | Due Date :30-Sep-2016

Finance Agreement :Section II.B.4 of Schedule 2 to the FA and GA | Description :The Recipient shall improve its computerizedfinancial management system in a manner acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :30-Nov-2012
Finance Agreement :Section II.B.5 of Schedule 2 to the FA and GA | Description :The Recipient shall engage an independent auditor| Due Date :28-Feb-2013

Finance Agreement :Section IV.B.1(b) of Schedule 2 to the FA and GA | Description :No withdrawals under Category 1 until (i) theRecipient have entered into a PBF Agency Agreement with a PPA and (ii) the said PPA has a PBF Manual finalized and (iii) said PPAhas opened a MCH Performance Account and a PPA Operation Account. | Due Date :30-Sep-2016
